    content: "Since 2021 responsible for coordination of activities aimed at creating and development of the National Digital Innovation Hubs Network in Poland. Managing projects supporting the digital and green transformation of enterprises. Has extensive experience in the implementation of business and R+D+I projects concerning Industry 4.0, foresight competences and futures studies. Former entrepreneur and academic lecturer. Since 2021 Member of the Program Council of the Factory of the Future Award in Poland. In the years 2017-2020, scientific researcher and project manager in the Innovation Strategies Department at Łukasiewicz Research Network - Institute for Sustainable Technologies. In the years 2016-2017 affiliated researcher at the Lord Ashcroft International Business School, Anglia Ruskin University. Doctor of Social Sciences in the discipline of Economics and Finance.", linkedin: "https://www.linkedin.com/in/anna-pajak-phd-63747810b/", twitter: "", domain: "", location: "",
